UID:bmi-foundation-babyface-award-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T131202Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: BMI Foundation Babyface Award 2026
DESCRIPTION:The BMI Foundation Babyface Award is an inaugural annual award 
 supporting emerging songwriters working in R&B\, hip-hop\, soul\, and musi
 c of the African diaspora. Founded with a $25\,000 investment from Wells F
 argo. AMOUNT: $10\,000 career grant plus artistic and business mentorship.
  ELIGIBILITY: ages 18-29 as of 30 June 2026\; US residents or those in US 
 territories\; submitted works must be unpublished and unassigned to major 
 labels or publishers (self-released works are eligible)\; co-written works
  are eligible if all writers meet the eligibility criteria (maximum 3 writ
 ers\; award split evenly). One application per person per year\; cannot su
 bmit the same work to multiple BMI Foundation programs. No affiliation wit
 h BMI required. APPLICATION MATERIALS: a 1-2 minute personal statement vid
 eo\; two audio files with anonymized lyric sheets (lyrics may be in any la
 nguage with English translation)\; and a description of the creative proce
 ss (audio\, visual\, or written format). No application fee. Apply via Goo
 gle Form at https://bmifoundation.org/by-application/babyfaceaward. Deadli
 ne: 30 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: BMI Foundation\nLocation: USA\; remote 
 application.\nAward: $10\,000 career grant plus artistic and business ment
 orship. No application fee.\nDuration: One-time award.\n\nMore: https://bm
 ifoundation.org/by-application/babyfaceaward?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://bmifoundation.org/by-application/babyfaceaward?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:USA\; remote application.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:adk-ems-berlin-stockholm-residency-2026-27@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T131202Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: AdK / EMS Berlin-Stockholm Bilateral Residency Program 20
 26-27
DESCRIPTION:A new bilateral residency collaboration between the Studio für
  Elektroakustische Musik at the Akademie der Künste in Berlin and Elektro
 nmusikstudion EMS in Stockholm. Four artists will be selected to develop a
 nd present new works in both cities\, with presentations at KONTAKTE 2027 
 in Berlin and at a corresponding event in Stockholm. The program supports 
 new artistic and technical initiatives at the intersection of sound\, musi
 c\, and technology in the field of time-based\, performative\, and digital
  arts. ELIGIBLE CATEGORIES: (1) new instrumental and live-electronic works
 \; (2) acousmatic music\, computer music\, radio art\, and other forms of 
 electroacoustic music and sound art\; (3) projects from artists of any dis
 cipline for whom sound is a central element\; (4) curatorial\, publishing\
 , and educational projects in sound-based art practice\, particularly thos
 e relating in content to the AdK Studio or EMS\; (5) independent research 
 in acoustics\, computer science\, or musicology -- specifically software d
 evelopment\, spatialization\, or network technologies. Open to individuals
  and groups. Project duration is flexible and arranged by agreement. SUPPO
 RT: travel and accommodation costs for Berlin and Stockholm covered\; pres
 entation fees paid for both venues. Selection is made by the director and 
 advisory board of the Studio für Elektroakustische Musik and the director
  of EMS\; decision is final with no legal entitlement to funding. Incomple
 te or late applications are not considered. This call supplements the Stud
 io's regular residency program (separate deadline June 30\, 2026 for July-
 December 2026 period). Apply exclusively via the online form at https://nc
 .adk.de/index.php/apps/forms/s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA. Questions: estudi
 o@adk.de. Deadline: 31 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Studio für Elektroakus
 tische Musik\, Akademie der Künste (Berlin) and Elektronmusikstudion EMS 
 (Stockholm)\nLocation: Berlin\, Germany and Stockholm\, Sweden\; travel an
 d accommodation covered for stays in both cities.\nAward: Travel and accom
 modation costs for stays in Berlin and Stockholm covered\; fees paid for p
 resentation at KONTAKTE Festival 2027 (Berlin) and for presentation in Sto
 ckholm. Amount not publicly stated. No application fee.\nDuration: Flexibl
 e\, by agreement\; works to be presented at KONTAKTE 2027 in Berlin and at
  a Stockholm presentation.\n\nMore: https://nc.adk.de/index.php/apps/forms
 /s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medi
 um=referral
URL:https://nc.adk.de/index.php/apps/forms/s/HD2nxbzqwgeMHWN6xHg9bQrA?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany and Stockholm\, Sweden\; travel and accommodation
  covered for stays in both cities.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:national-gallery-iceland-cusp-residency-reykjavik-2027@artificialnouvea
 u.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260723T131202Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260903
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260904
SUMMARY:Deadline: National Gallery of Iceland: CUSP Artist Residency (Reykj
 avik 2027)
DESCRIPTION:The National Gallery of Iceland announces an artist residency o
 pen call under its CUSP program\, a European cooperation project funded th
 rough Creative Europe's Culture grant. Artists working in complex media or
  emerging technologies (e.g. generative AI\, custom sensors\, sound\, soft
 ware-based\, blockchain\, physical and digital hybrid) are invited to appl
 y. This is the first of four residency stays offered to different artists 
 through the program\, one in each of the participating countries (Iceland\
 , Norway\, Czechia\, and Ukraine)\, followed by two micro residencies in t
 he Netherlands and Iceland. The programme brings together artists working 
 in time-based media with museum professionals\, conservators\, and technol
 ogy specialists developing preservation and conservation methodologies to 
 ensure the long-term endurance of artworks. The selected artist will meet 
 with a preservation specialist or conservator specializing in time-based m
 edia art for an in-depth artist interview addressing the preservation need
 s of their medium\, and will present their body of work and working method
 s publicly during an open-lab masterclass designed in collaboration with t
 he museum. RESIDENCY: up to four weeks in early 2027 in Reykjavik\, exact 
 dates arranged with the selected artist. WHAT IS PROVIDED: accommodation a
 nd working space\; a travel and subsistence stipend\; an artist fee for th
 e open lab/masterclass\; and possibly hardware and software depending on t
 he artist's request and museum means. ELIGIBILITY: international artists b
 ased outside Iceland\; applicants must be residents of any of the 27 EU me
 mber states or of non-EU countries with association agreements (EFTA/EEA m
 embers\, acceding countries\, candidate countries\, and European Neighbour
 hood Policy countries). APPLICATION: complete the application form with fu
 ll name\, country of residence\, gender identity\, contact information\, a
 n artistic statement (max 2500 characters)\, a motivation letter (max 2500
  characters)\, a draft idea of the public workshop or masterclass (max 100
 0 characters)\, links to social media/professional websites\, and a CV and
  portfolio upload (max 10MB each). DEADLINE: 3 September 2026 at 23:59 GMT
 . ABOUT CUSP: Creative Understanding\, Saving and Preserving Time-Based Me
 dia Art is a transnational cooperation project co-funded by the EU's Creat
 ive Europe Culture grant\, led by the National Gallery of Iceland with Nas
 jonalmuseet (Norway)\, LI-MA (Netherlands)\, Vasulka Kitchen (Czechia)\, a
 nd Mystetskyi Art Arsenal (Ukraine)\, focused on preserving and presenting
  time-based media art. Inquiries: cusp.residency.is [at] gmail.com.\n\nOrg
 anisation: National Gallery of Iceland (Listasafn Islands)\, CUSP project\
 nLocation: Reykjavik\, Iceland. Residency hosted by the National Gallery o
 f Iceland.\nAward: Accommodation and working space for the residency\; tra
 vel and subsistence stipend\; an artist fee for collaborating in the open-
 lab/masterclass\; and\, depending on the artist's request and museum means
 \, hardware and software for the working space. No application fee.\nDurat
 ion: Up to four weeks\, taking place in early 2027\, with exact dates arra
 nged with the selected artist.\n\nMore: https://www.listasafn.is/en/art/ne
 ws-vasulka-stofa/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://www.listasafn.is/en/art/news-vasulka-stofa/?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Reykjavik\, Iceland. Residency hosted by the National Gallery of I
 celand.
END:VEVENT
